50|$|The Charity Commission for England and Wales has the {{statutory}} power {{to apply the}} <b>cy-près</b> doctrine {{on behalf of a}} charity where, for example, no trustees remain in a charity or the necessary mandate cannot be agreed. These powers extend to a corporate charity or unincorporated association (which the common law rules may not cover). Similar powers apply to the equivalent bodies in Northern Ireland and Scotland. The <b>cy-près</b> doctrine will not be applied where a charity has alternative powers to redirect its funds under its constitution.|$|E
