50|$|When the {{original}} {{objective of the}} settlor or the testator became impossible, impracticable, or illegal to perform, the <b>cy-près</b> doctrine allows the court to amend {{the terms of the}} charitable trust as closely as possible to {{the original}} intention of the testator or settlor to prevent the trust from failing.|$|E
